OL,3,C'Paused' mesh operations still being
OL,4,Ccarried out at North Wales Health Board
OL,6,FIn its response, Aneurin Bevan
OL,7,FUniversity Health Board said it did
OL,8,Fnot have any data after June 2018, 'as
OL,9,Fthese procedures were paused
OL,10,Findefinitely'.
OL,12,FThe Welsh Government says vaginal mesh
OL,13,Fto treat stress urinary incontinence
OL,14,Fshould only be used if there is no
OL,15,Fviable alternative and after close and
OL,16,Fcomprehensive consultation between
OL,17,Fpatient and clinician. Some procedures
OL,18,Fare allowed under certain
OL,19,Fcircumstances and under high vigilance
OL,20,Fscrutiny arrangements, but this will
OL,21,Fbe a clinical decision.
